(223, 1, '2021-08-08 08:40:47', '2021-08-08 08:40:47', '<div class=\"celwidget\" data-csa-c-id=\"occhfb-h1biw0-rb8cur-i9u1j3\" data-cel-widget=\"dpx-editorial-reviews_csm_instrumentation_wrapper\">\r\n<div id=\"editorialReviews_feature_div\" class=\"celwidget\" data-feature-name=\"editorialReviews\" data-csa-c-id=\"nqy6el-xl0jq2-lqtm4c-xyonzb\" data-cel-widget=\"editorialReviews_feature_div\">\r\n<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-small a-padding-base\">\r\n<h3>About the Author</h3>\r\n<div class=\"a-section a-spacing-small a-padding-small\">Inio Asano, a bona fide earthling, was born in Ibaraki, Japan, in 1980. In 2001, his short story “Uchu kara Konnichiwa” (Hello from Outer Space) won the first Sunday GX Rookie Prize. Later, GX published his series <i>Subarashii Sekai</i>, available in English from VIZ Media as <i>What a Wonderful World!</i> His other works include <i>Hikari no Machi</i> (City of Light), <i>Nijigahara Holograph</i> and <i>Umibe no Onna no Ko</i> (<i>A Girl on the Shore</i>), as well as <i>solanin</i> and <i>Goodnight Punpun</i>, also available from VIZ Media.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"celwidget\" data-csa-c-id=\"h0my36-1g41od-2l5evx-rax0yr\" data-cel-widget=\"dpx-detail-bullets_csm_instrumentation_wrapper\">\r\n<div id=\"detailBullets_feature_div\" class=\"celwidget\" data-feature-name=\"detailBullets\" data-csa-c-id=\"xbvrxh-rf3mcw-4lwpw6-8fslyh\" data-cel-widget=\"detailBullets_feature_div\">\r\n<div id=\"detailBulletsWrapper_feature_div\" class=\"a-section feature detail-bullets-wrapper bucket\" data-feature-name=\"detailBullets\" data-template-name=\"detailBullets\" data-cel-widget=\"detailBulletsWrapper_feature_div\">\r\n\r\n<hr class=\"a-divider-normal bucketDivider\" aria-hidden=\"true\" />\r\n\r\n<h2>Product details</h2>\r\n<div id=\"detailBullets_feature_div\">\r\n<ul class=\"a-unordered-list a-nostyle a-vertical a-spacing-none detail-bullet-list\">\r\n 	<li><span class=\"a-list-item\"><span class=\"a-text-bold\">